A MASSIVE CROW stands near the Tree. A bloody head is gripped tight in its talons.
Upon the partyâ€™s arrival, it lets out an earsplitting CAW, before flitting up into the branches. 
THE HERO, LORATH, and NEYRELLE approach the TREE OF WHISPERS.
HUNDREDS OF HEADS in various states of decay hang from countless branches that stretch out in all directions.
The heads whisper constantly. Their eyes are closed.
Neyrelle approaches the heads with curiosity, leaning in to examine one.
Suddenly, the background whispering ceases.
She jumps as all the heads abruptly swivel to face her, opening what eyes still remain to stare directly at her.
Lorath starts. He is cautious and alert. One head addresses Neyrelle.

Neyrelle whips around to look at all the heads in wonder.
They rotate to follow her movements, then shift attention when Lorath steps forward.
Neyrelle steps forward to speak. Lorath watches hesitantly, on his guard.
The Tree takes a moment to deliberate.
At this, some heads snicker in the background.

The eyes of the heads slip shut again and the mouths resume their discordant whispering.
The heads rotate back to their original positions.
